author: Dolan Media Newswires
title: J&L takes Wisconsin to court over veterans project
text:
Apartment Sales Tracker Home / News / J&L takes Wisconsin to court over veterans project LouAnne Berg, chief executive of Hudson-based J&L Steel and Electrical Services, is suing the state of Wisconsin to recover $217,499 in a dispute over a veterans home project in Chippewa Falls. (File photo: Bill Klotz) J&L takes Wisconsin to court over veterans project By: Dolan Media Newswires July 31, 2015 4:03 pm 0 An electrical contractor who is suing the state in a dispute over a Chippewa Falls veterans home project will be going to trial early next year, despite entering into mediation with some of the parties she is suing.
